        <h2>Amazium Forms</h2>
        <p>Thanks to the awesome <a href="https://github.com/shahrukhomar" target="_blank">Shahrukh Omar </a>who has made it possible to show the label of an input when the user starts 
          typing in a field so know what each field is. All you will need to do is add 
          css class nysmnyd-labels 
          to your form and make sure you have the Amazium.js file included and you too 
          will have fancy show/hide lables on your inputs.
        </p>
        <form name="" method="" action="" class="nysmnyd-labels">
          <section class="row">
            <article class="grid_4">
